What is nimiSlides?

What is nimiSlides?

  • Nimib üê≥ theme based on Reveal.js

  • Powered by Nim üëë

  • Elegant DSL-based API

Why nimib?

Why nimib?

  • Powerful

    • Nim's meta programming

Incremental Lists

Incremental Lists

  • Back again

A few practical examples

Using Templates

Using Templates

slide(slideOptions(autoAnimate=true)):
  nbText: "## Animate header"
slide(slideOptions(autoAnimate=true)):
  nbText: "## Animate header"
  nbText: "Animate this"
slide(slideOptions(autoAnimate=true)):
  nbText: "## Animate header"
  nbText: "Animate this"
  nbText: "And this"

Let's make our lifes easier and define a template for this!

Using Templates

template slideAutoAnimate(body: untyped) =
  slide(slideOptions(autoAnimate=true)):
    body

slideAutoAnimate:
  nbText: "## Animate header"

Example: Histogram of Gaussian for different N

Loops ‚ôªÔ∏è + Generate images üñºÔ∏è

for n in [50, 100, 1000, 10000]:
  let filename = &"gauss-{n}.png"
  let samples = newSeqWith[float](n, gauss(0.0, 1.0))
  let df = toDf(samples)
  ggplot(df, aes("samples")) +
    geom_histogram(fillColor="green") +
    ggsave(filename)

  slide:
    nbText: &"## Gauss Samples (N = {n})"
    nbImage(filename)
